<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181922" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole petersoni Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole petersoni Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petersoni">Pheidole petersoni</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="486">types INBio.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">etymology Named in honor of the great naturalist and artist Roger Tory Peterson, whose field-guide style inspired the form of the drawings used in this monograph.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">
diagnosis A very distinctive large member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group distinguished by its unique sculpturing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">Major: brown; mesopleuron and side of propodeum irregularly rugoreticulate; center and sides of pronotum smooth and shiny or at most with scattered punctures; humerus in dorsal-oblique view raised prominently.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="486">
Minor: yellow; mesopleuron and side of propodeum irregularly rugoreticulate; center and sides of pronotum smooth and shiny or at most with scattered punctures; humerus in dorsal-oblique view a pointed, &quot;sharkfin&quot; shape; occiput narrow surmounted by a thin collar. Similar in body form to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181870" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole erratilis Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erratilis">erratilis</taxonomicName>
of Costa Rica, which species lacks the rugoreticulum, has longer pilosity, and more extensive cephalic carinulae. See also the less similar 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181839" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole angulifera Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulifera">angulifera</taxonomicName>
, ecuadorana, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:182066" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole polita Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole polita Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="polita">polita</taxonomicName>
(in the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34070" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tristis (Smith)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
group), 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181939" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole schmalzi Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schmalzi">schmalzi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181946" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole styrax Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole styrax Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styrax">styrax</taxonomicName>
. measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 1.08, HL 1.14, SL 0.64, EL 0.18, PW 0.58. Paratype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.66, SL 0.66, EL 0.14, PW 0.40.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="486">Color Major: medium to dark and slightly reddish brown, tarsi light yellowish brown. Minor: medium brown, tarsi brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="486">Biology New second-growth forest, on bananas and Piper; a colony was found nesting in a dead Piper stem (Longino 1997).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
